## Overview

Create a full-featured card detail panel that opens when clicking a Kanban card. This transforms tasks from minimal card views to rich, interactive detail views with all metadata, tabs for checklist/comments/activity, and inline editing.

**User Problem:**
- Cards show minimal info (title snippet, tags, due date)
- No way to see full description, add comments, or manage checklist
- Need to edit card → opens inline form (cramped, limited functionality)

**Solution:**
Full-screen detail panel (modal) with:
- Left side: All task metadata (title, description, dates, priority, tags, assignee)
- Right side: Tabs (Checklist / Comments / Activity Log)
- Inline editing for all fields
- Keyboard shortcuts (Esc to close, Cmd+Enter to save)
- Mobile responsive (full screen on mobile, centered modal on desktop)

---

## Problem Statement

### Current Behavior

**Kanban Cards (Current):**
- Click card → Inline edit mode appears
- Shows: Title input, description textarea, priority dropdown, tags
- Limited space (squeezed into card)
- No room for checklist, comments, or activity log
- Hard to see full task context

**What's Missing:**
- No dedicated "detail view" for tasks
- No tabbed interface for different task aspects
- No way to see activity history
- No space for rich features (comments, checklist, attachments future)

### Desired Behavior

**Click Card → Card Detail Panel Opens:**
- **Left Side (60%)**: Task metadata
  - Title (large, editable)
  - Description (full textarea, expandable)
  - Due date (date picker)
  - Priority (dropdown)
  - Tags (tag input with add/remove)
  - Status (column dropdown)
  - Assignee (future: user dropdown, for now: text input)
- **Right Side (40%)**: Tabbed sections
  - **Checklist Tab**: Subtasks with progress bar
  - **Comments Tab**: Threaded discussions
  - **Activity Tab**: Timeline of changes
- **Keyboard Shortcuts:**
  - `Esc` → Close panel
  - `Cmd+Enter` / `Ctrl+Enter` → Save and close
  - `Tab` / `Shift+Tab` → Navigate fields
- **Mobile Responsive:**
  - Mobile: Full screen (100% width/height)
  - Tablet: 90% width, centered
  - Desktop: 80% width (max 1200px), centered

